    ([Dream-walking], [Intimate, surreal, emotionally raw. Characters meet in a space that feels unreal, which makes honesty easier. In #emph[Strange the Dreamer], the romance between Lazlo and Sarai is built entirely through dream-sharing before they can touch in waking life: intimacy before embodiment. The dream space makes recognition possible where reality wouldn't allow it.], [Only works during sleep; hard to verify if it was real; vulnerability of being found in dreams. Dreams can also be manipulated, making them the highest-misunderstanding channel.]),
    ([Enchanted objects (mirrors, journals, coins)], [Tangible, keepable, rereadable. The object itself becomes precious, a third presence in the relationship that gets carried, hidden, touched, and protected. Unlike telepathy, which leaves no trace, a journal entry is proof of devotion, and losing the object becomes a credible emotional catastrophe. In #emph[ACOTAR], the bargain tattoo functions as an enchanted object: a sensory organ through which Rhysand can send physical feelings and see through Feyre's eyes. The second, hidden tattoo becomes a private communication channel during Feyre's spy mission.], [Can be lost, stolen, intercepted, or destroyed. Limited bandwidth. The object's magic may also have its own agenda, turning a romantic promise into a trap.]),
    ([Magical bonds (soul bonds, mating bonds)], [Involuntary, inescapable. Emotions or sensations bleed across the bond whether wanted or not. In #emph[Fourth Wing], the dragon-mated bond between Violet and Xaden creates sensory overload during intimate moments and involuntary truth-sharing. Xaden's feelings bleed into Violet's consciousness even when he refuses to voice them aloud. In #emph[ACOTAR], the mating bond can signal injury, absence, or death: when the bond goes silent, it means the worst has happened.], [Loss of privacy, inability to hide pain or desire, bond may be unwanted initially. Bonds can be rejected but rarely erased; the "tug" persists, which means romance must be negotiated inside a permanent system rather than chosen fresh.]),
